title: Kaggle Competition - Part III
description:
NEXT MEETUP - October 1st (Wednesday)

-- NO MEETUP THIS WEEK!! --

Let's continue the Titanic challenge. In this next meetup (October 1st) we are continuing to follow this great tutorial (https://github.com/wehrley/wehrley.github.io/blob/master/SOUPTONUTS.md).

We'll be covering the last 3 parts:

• Fitting a Model

• Model Evaluation

• Cast Your Votes

Make sure that you have tried out the previous parts (Getting the Data Into R and Data Munging) - especially if you missed the last meetup.

I'll be updating the R-ladies repository at Github by the end of this week: https://github.com/R-ladies

Also, the slide deck (https://github.com/R-ladies/ProjectTemplate) used on the "Kaggle Competition - Part" I is now available at github.

* If you have questions, feel free to use slack: https://r-ladies.slack.com/

title: Kaggle Competition - Part II
description:
Kaggle Competition

The movie Titanic was great, and our team effort to figure out who lived and who died will be just as fantastic. This is a great opportunity to improve our data analysis and R skills on a large dataset.

We are going to have 3 meetings: August 28th, September 4th and September 11th.

Everyone is welcome to join. Even if you are not very experienced, you can still listen in on the discussions.

=================================================

https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic-gettingStarted

Predict survival on the Titanic (with tutorials in R)

This Kaggle "Getting Started" Competition provides an ideal starting place for people who may not have a lot of experience in data science and machine learning. The data is highly structured, and we provide tutorials.

There is no such thing as a stupid question; we guarantee someone else will be wondering the same thing!

title: Kaggle Competition - Part I
description:
R-ladies to enter Kaggle Competition!

The movie Titanic was great, and our team effort to figure out who lived and who died will be just as fantastic. This is a great opportunity to improve our data analysis and R skills on a large dataset.

We are going to have 3 meetings: August 28th, September 4th and September 11th.

Everyone is welcome to join. Even if you are not very experienced, you can still listen in on the discussions.

Agenda:

6:00pm - 6:30pm: Networking + Installing R and RStudio

6:30pm - 7:00 pm: Sign up at Kaggle, download the data

7:00 pm - 7:30pm: Set up a new data analysis project using ProjectTemplate (http://projecttemplate.net/)

7:30pm - 9:00pm - Data Exploration (plots, summaries, tables, etc)

* We will have snacks and drinks provided by Alpine Data Labs (http://alpinenow.com)

=================================================

https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic-gettingStarted

Predict survival on the Titanic (with tutorials in Excel, Python, R, and an introduction to Random Forests)

This Kaggle "Getting Started" Competition provides an ideal starting place for people who may not have a lot of experience in data science and machine learning. The data is highly structured, and we provide tutorials of increasing complexity for using Excel, Python, pandas in Python, and a Random Forest in Python (see links in the sidebar).

We also have links to tutorials using R instead. Please use the forums freely and as much as you like.

There is no such thing as a stupid question; we guarantee someone else will be wondering the same thing!

title: useR! 2014
description:
This year the main and most important R conference, useR! (http://user2014.stat.ucla.edu/), will be in Los Angeles.

The conference starts on June 30th and ends on July 3rd.

There will be a lot of awesome tutorials (http://user2014.stat.ucla.edu/#tutorials) and a lot of great talks and posters! It will be a great opportunity to meet the R rockstars and to learn more!

The registration is open. Just got to this link: http://user2014.stat.ucla.edu/#registration . There is a discount if you register before May 10th.

If you have any question, please feel free to contact me: gabkroz@gmail.com

I'd love to see a lot of R-ladies there!

title: Ladies' Night - Empowering Women in the Workplace
description:
Hey Ladies!

Do you care about women empowerment and career development? Would you like to enjoy a fun and inspiring moment with like-minded ladies?

Then join us on March 19 for our "Ladies' Night" unconference and networking event dedicated to women in STEM.

Panel and small group discussions, networking opportunities, giveaways, wine, cheese, chocolate and more await you!

DON'T FORGET TO GET YOUR TICKETS HERE:

http://ladiesnight-alpine.eventbrite.com/?aff=rladies (https://ladiesnight-alpine.eventbrite.com/).

Lineup:

Jennifer Arguello, Senior Tech Advisor, Kapor Center for Social Impact

Nina Bhatti, Advisory board of the Anita Borg Institute for Women in Technology

Angie Chang, Director of Growth at Hackbright Academy

Hulya Emir-Farinas, Sr. Principal Data Scientist at Pivotal

Leann Pereira, Founder and CEO at Recruiter.net, LLC

Cheryl Porro, SVP of Technology & Products for the salesforce.com Foundation

Gabriela de Queiroz, Founder of R-ladies and Data Scientist at Alpine Data Labs

More names to be announced soon!

Program:

6:00 - 6:30 Registration and Networking

6:30 - 7:00 Welcome speech and lightning talks

7:00 - 8:00 Panel Discussion

8:00 - 9:00 Small Group Discussions and more Networking

+ Wine, Cheese, Unlimited Chocolate and Giveaways

Questions and suggestions welcome! More info to come soon.

This event is FREE and limited to 150 ladies.

title: Stanford Online Class Statistical Learning - Week 1
description:
Hello R-ladies!

For the first time the professors from Stanford, Trevor Hastie and Rob Tibshirani, will be teaching an online course. They have been leaders in the field of statistical and machine learning.

Here is the link:

https://class.stanford.edu/courses/HumanitiesScience/StatLearning/Winter2014/about

I'm very excited to announce that we are going to have a weekly study group during the period of the class. We'll meet every Thursday from 6pm to 9pm at Alpine Data Labs (https://maps.google.com/maps?ie=UTF-8&q=Alpine+Data+Labs&fb=1&gl=us&hq=alpine+data+labs&hnear=0x80859a6d00690021:0x4a501367f076adff,San+Francisco,+CA&cid=9890511290876331625&ei=ZoCzUoqXFsn6oASFo4LQAg&ved=0CKgBEPwSMAo).

PREREQUISITES:

First courses in statistics, linear algebra, and computing. (I would also add: some familiarity with R)

Be sure to bring your laptop.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Please, don't RSVP if:

. You think you'll not be able to make it.

* Also, people that RSVPed several times and never showed up, you'll be automatically redirected to the waiting list or not attending.

Note: this meetup is for women only; emphatically trans & queer friendly!
